In this code, we use two nested loops to iterate over the rows and columns of the multiplication table. The outer loop iterates from 1 to the given number `n` to control the number of rows. The inner loop also iterates from 1 to `n` to control the number of columns.

Inside the inner loop, we calculate the product of the current row number `i` and the current column number `j` using the expression `i * j`. We then print the result followed by a space.

